                        width="500"
                        src="https://github.com/atippaz/bomberman-v2/blob/master/client/src/asset/images/player/Player_idle.gif?raw=true"
                        alt="project"
                      />
                    </div>
                    <div class="text-[1.2rem]">
                      <p>
                        <strong>Bomberman</strong> is a game development project
                        using C# and Windows Forms GUI, created without a game engine.
                        It focused on practicing object-oriented programming (OOP)
                        and game design.
                      </p>
                      <p>
                        The game was developed in collaboration with two
                        friends—one of them designed and created the UI for the
                        game windows, while I handled the core game logic and
                        controls. The technology stack used includes C# and the
                        .NET Framework. There are plans to expand the game for
                        the web, utilizing <em>Vue</em> and <em>Pixi</em> for the
                        web-based version.
                      </p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="flex justify-end gap-2">
                    <a
                      href="https://github.com/atippaz/BomberMan"
                      class="btn btn-primary my-4">Repository</a
